caption: Delicious. I live around the corner and pass this place all the time, but I’ve never been in. I ordered the chicken paillard for takeout, and for $16, you get two big thin sliced chicken breasts, pasta, salad, and focaccia. Super fresh and flavorful.

(Translated by Google) I was very disappointed in your Brooklyn restaurant, I went to celebrate his birthday with my partner and it was somewhat disappointing, the place neglected, there was not like a waiter who could guide us about the pasta, and when we asked for the pasta the chicken was cold, we asked the avocado salad the avocado was sour. We are not happy to return  (Original) Quede muy decepcionada de su restaurante de Brooklyn, fui a celebrar con mi pareja su cumpleaños y fue algo decepcionante, el lugar descuidado, no había como un mesero que nos pudiera orientar sobre las pastas, y cuando pedimos la pasta el pollo estaba frío, pedimos la ensalada de aguacate el aguacate estaba amargo. No quedamos con gusto de volver

Sorry guys. Despite a lovely server ,food left much to be desired. Veal fra diabolo sauce was without heat,looked love me vodka sauce and the fresh sliced baby tomatoes were bitter. Bread was stale . Chocolate mouse was a cake slice from a box. Very uninspired.
Excellent.  Can't wait to eat again.
Every single fish was delicious.  Very comfortable atmosphere. Super friendly staff.
Exceptional and fresh food, I love the mood this spot has, and the employees were helpful. I will surely visit here again.

Looking for amazing pasta? Stop by here as they make their own in-house. They have a great variety to choose from and their sauces are amazing as well.  Try the ravioli or get one of their pesto sauces to start. Their Alfredo sauce is good enough yo eat by itself. The drinks will keep you nice and toasty, my new favorite is the apple martini.

I came here last night and their were two people sitting inside eating. Before going in I called them on the phone about 10pm and they answered, I asked if I was able to get a cappuccino before walking in because I knew they might be closed. The guy on the phone told me “Yes Yess, no problem, just for a cappuccino come on in.” So I sent in my husband and the man tells him that the cappuccino machine was off. My husband is a black man and I felt like he was discriminated against! It’s all good because I will NEVER come back here for that reason and will be sure to let people know about my negative experience!
This spot is awesome! Good prices, big dishes and the staff members are consistently nice.
Nice people ....Easy pasta and pomodoro !

Cafe Buon Gusto Has done a magical job creating an outdoor environment in their private garden to dine safely during Covid. The staff is professional, friendly, and accommodating, the food is delicious and very reasonably priced Italian, and the ambience is magical with potted trees, beautiful flowers and plants, and twinkling lights. We have been several times and highly recommend it!
This place is worth trying. They have big portions for convenient rates. Constantly well kept and with fantastic character. Would recommend to others.

Ordered delivery twice from this place and was really impressed. Pesto, carbonara, and Alfredo sauces were on point, sizes were reasonable for the price, and deliveries went off without a hitch.  Haven’t tried other Italian places in the area yet (just moved into area) but I’d recommend this place to anyone who loves simple Italian pasta dishes.  EDIT:  Had a meal here that was well below the standard articulated above, so I'm subtracting half a star. The food that was delivered tasted off (the cream sauces in particular were not fresh at all, and the pesto had a poorer texture than when I previously ate there).  I'm rounding up because of all the quality experiences I've had here, but I wanted to note the inconsistency here.
Eating in the garden on a balmy summer evening is lovely. Service and food are always good.
The food is tasty. The service is fast. The waiters are nice. Also, the restaurant has a beautiful outdoor backyard seating. Great ambiance.

This is one of my favorite restaurants in the area - definitely my favorite for pastas! I’ve been here dozens of times, for dine in and take out. They are taking lots of COVID precautions and I’ve always get so safe getting food from here. I will definitely continue to dine here for the amazing pasta!
Friendly service and very good food, octopus and ravioli!!!
Calamari was bland and oily.  Main course was too salty.

I've been coming here for over 25 years and I am still in love. I am sorry they moved, but they are still on the same street. I took myself out for a meal last night and took pictures of everything I ate because it was so beautiful.
I love it Great food and excellent service
Atmosphere pleasant. Didnt care for the food was too bland.
The worst. Food is fake Italian and flavorless. Delivery is usually wrong. Management is rude.
The worst service used to be good
This spot is worth a try. They have big portions for affordable rates. Constantly neat and with awesome vibes. Will come visit again.
Good, but nothing to write home about.  Prix Fixe menu is a good deal, though.

Thank you! We got 3 different estimate for a part replacement and This company had the best price by far from other companies. They even gave us the option for a payment plan without %. Great deal!

Worst service I have ever experienced by far. Agreed to meet my sister there.  Upon being seated I asked for a glass of cabernet which they brought right away then they never came back..  45 minutes of being ignored with a server going to and from and no n acknowledgement whatsoever.  I finally stopped him and told him I  was ready to order and he says "I will be right back".  5 minutes  later WOW!!! he took my order.  Once my sister  gets there she orders and they never came back to check on us .  Had to flag him  down again for the bill..  I would have gotten up within 20 minutes and walked out but didnt want to send my sister from place to place so just hang tight.  One thing's for sure.   Never will return
I ordered as at 10 pm and it was 11 pm and my food was not arriving yet, and I called and it was closed, they charged me and they did not give me an explanation

Beautiful little Italian spot. Home made pasta, white table clothes and the whole host of wonderful experiences.  We booked for a date night on the 4th and walked down a few blocks to enjoy the fireworks.  Food was delightful and appealed to all of your senses. High quality and reminiscent of our meals in Italy. Quite a pleasing selection and choices for pasta and non pasta lovers of Italian food.
Very accommodating. Decent wine list. Excellent salads

Scheduled a brunch for 17 people after my daughter's baptism and NOBODY - no staff, chefs, waiters, no one - was there. We were not allowed to enter or sit until an hour of waiting outside (with babies) and when we were seated, we were told we could not order because there was no chef on site.  It was a terrible, embarrassing situation for me and shameful for the restaurant. Despite multiple calls to confirm details with the owner, we were let down by the restaurant and forced to leave hungry and frustrated with no answers.  When I spoke to the owner the next day, he acknowledged the lapses, but provided no resolution or explanation other than blame his irresponsible staff. I do not recommend this place for any events you plan to have. They are unreliable and frankly, ruined my daughter's baptism day.
Nice quite restaurant and thr srafood linguini with white sauce was delicious.
Love it!! This is my favorite movie theater.  Multicultural atmosphere no drama fast easy quick service.  Movie theater never ever had a odor!
The presentation looks amazing and the smell is nice. Very affordable prices!
I had salmon,  my friend had sole fillet, both on dinner set, both were delicious.  Sole fillet was very excellent...

Better bread than any other italian restaurant I've been to in recent years, and delicious ravioli. Also a very friendly wait staff and a relaxed yet classy atmosphere that feels open to everyone. Would love to go back and try more items on the menu.

I was in Brooklyn for a conference and decided to stop by my company's Brooklyn office to work for the day. Come lunchtime, a coworker suggested this "new place that they'd found".  Needless to say, the food was amazing!! I've never been to Italy, but I imagine this is what authentic Italian food tastes like... Nothing at all like Olive Garden.  My only complaint is the cost (especially since it was just lunch), but I guess that's to be expected in NY.  Will definitely go back if/when I'm in the area.

Oh! How this place has fallen from grace. Signature cocktails were bland and uninspiring.    The fried calamari was straight out of a freezer bag. Soups bordered on the bizarre.  My tomato soup was infused with garlic. 🤯.  My companion complained about her minestrone.  Black ink pasta was squishy bordering on inedible.  Best dish was the house salad.  On the plus side it was quiet and suitable for conversation and we stayed until the place closed and emptied out without being hassled.
One of our favorite Italian restaurants on Montague street in Brooklyn Heights
Nice quaint place food was good
Incredible vodka sauce and build your own pasta adventure!  Everything we tried was amazing!
Food was delicious..Prices good
Proper Italian place downtown

We were pleasantly surprised by this gem hidden in plain sight. We all enjoyed our meals and the service was excellent. Contrary to the review below of the spaghetti and meatballs, I ordered the exact same dish and was very pleased. Served medium al dente. Will definitely be back.
(Translated by Google) Good place to eat Italian food, very friendly service and delicious food  (Original) Buen lugar para comer comida italiana, el servicio muy amable y la comida riquisimaa
Their gluten free options are a bit limited (just gf penne) but the sauces are excellent.

I brought my girlfriend here for our anniversary and not only did they ignore us half the time but they also messed up my order twice. I ordered the black linguine and it came out soggy and watery as hell like it was stuck in a microwave. I ate what I could with her and tried to make the best out of it before we left. I’m only leaving two stars because they attempted to apologize for all the mistakes but my experience was very subpar from what I was expecting.

Do not eat or order from here. This is not Italian. I ordered a very simple spaghetti and meatballs with a mixed green salad. The salad was basic but fine. Mixed greens and two slices of tomato. So I guess that’s fine. The spaghetti wasn’t spaghetti. It was a flat thin noodle more like a pad Thai noodle with marinara. The marinara/sauce itself was terrible. The meatballs were gray and tasted a week old. I ate the salad and after a few bites, threw the pasta in the trash. I am an equal opportunity eater, not at all picky. And while I understand every restaurant and every cook has a bad night, this was truly awful and warrants someone’s attention.
Great food, great bread, and wonderful service.
Food is amazing! Had mussels and calamari as an appetizer then chicken parm for dinner. Good service by several employees who were all friendly.
Always welcoming
Amazing!
One of the best bets for lunch on Montague Street. Classy service and great food. Recently returned for a bowl of pasta Bolognese on a cold day. Excellent and soul warming!
One of the waiters was annoying, and food was nothing special. Never visit and don't recommend anyone to visit.

The wait staff was amazing, threw some humor at our wonderful waitress by poking fun at my empty menu page and she gave it right back, was so funny!  The owner stopped by several times and we chatted with him outside about beer back in his home country.  Really made our experience great!  Thank you Caffe Buon Gusto!!

Stopped in here since I was in the area and heard good things about the one in Manhattan. I ordered take out for about four of us including kids. Some of our pasta dishes included chicken and it was bland. It literally looked like they boiled chunks of chicken and threw it in the dish. We also ordered vegetables which were laughable, portion size was extremely small, container was only quarter way filled. We ended up having to get fast food after wasting $85.

Everything about this place was perfection. Our hostess was hilarious and personable. The food was out of this world and we chatted it up with one of the owners outside for a bit who was down to earth and awesome. Can't recommend this place enough.

When I called, I was told that it was ordered through Seamless so nothing they can do. Don't order from here.

The customer service is unbeatble here. Nando, the main chef was so sweet and always keeps a check on his customers and asks them if they need anything. The staff here are so kind, and very engaging. Now for the food, it’s totally delicious and deserts are top notch as well. The pasta isn’t superbly expensive and it’s amazing for the price. If you want to dine in a nice area. This is the place! We sat outdoors and it was so refreshing. They really treated as well and even put desert on the house. Would recommend anyone to go here. The staff won my heart the most. 💓
i had their crab meat ravioli and it just blew my mind. would visit again!!!

yuck. service was weird—my boyfriend asked where their fish was sourced from—the manager said “i don’t know, the company” and seemed annoyed that he asked. his soup was scalding hot and burned the inside of his mouth. he said his salmon was like a freezer dinner. the potatoes that came with my omelette were ice cold and my omelette was tasteless. flies around the restaurant that kept landing on us. decor is outdated and our tablecloth was dirty. annoyed that i spent $30 for such a disappointing meal. we won’t be back.

Fantastic service! I was reviewing the menu when the manager came over to me and made me feel so comfortable that I had to go in. All the servers were amazing and I believe they share the tip. I frequented Caffe Buon Gusto for years. We were always greeted warmly right as we stepped in the door and their food is absolutely amazing. I usually get the linguini alfredo pasta and cheese tortellini with vodka sauce. I have never been disappointed with the service or food here. My husband and I moved out of state and still talk about this restuarant regularly; we miss it so much! Hope you all are well and cannot wait to visit when we are back in NYC!

This the epitome of a mom and pops restaurant in nyc. Friendly servers, homemade food and good overall food. They start you off with several types of homemade bread: pizza, ciabatta, Frenc that is fresh and delicious. We ordered the homemade fettuccini with pomodoro and ricotta - huge dish and perfectly cooked. They serve several types of homemade pasta and about 7 types of sauces.. wish I️ could’ve tried them all! My mom had a tortellini with spicy pomodoro sauce and my bf the Marsala veal with mozzarella and side of pasta. Both dishes beautiful cooked and just the right amount. They gave us a complimentary tiramisu for dessert! They def won our hearts and a good tip! Would come again

Good service for a decent group of people.  The lasagna isnt great, clearly prepared and was a bit soggy. The waitress was nice but had difficulty spliting the check.

Pleasant enough experience!  Shrimp with prosciutto was perky and fun, risotto was creamy and hearty. Pizza bread and focaccia so soft and yummy. Desserts were meh and needed a kick. One of my old haunts in Bklyn Heights and places I miss most from my years there. The linguine lobster and al filetto salad are absolutely fantastic! Food is decent and service is friendly, but not the best Italian in the area. Popularity due more to its excellent location on Montague St and its proximity to the courthouses, making it a favorite among judges and lawyers.

DO NOT EAT HERE!!  I have never posted a restaurant review before. And I have never been as unhappy upon leaving a restaurant as I was when I left Caffe Buon Gusto.  The service was downright offensive. The maitre d' / owner(?) was rude and condescending. He appeared at our table merely to countermand a suggestion by his own wait staff. (The staff, to their credit, repeatedly approached us to apologize.)  The food was deeply ordinarily. My son said that his chicken tasted liked french toast. Go figure.  But nothing compares to the service, or plumbs the depths as deeply, as what we experienced at this establishment.  All in all, a profoundly disappointing experience. As long time Heights residents, Caffe Buon Gusto exceeded all of our expectations and to a degree that before this evening I would not have thought possible. Not only did I leave the restaurant hungry, and disappointed by the food, but actually downright angry about having made the mistake of walking in the door.  Save your time, and your money, and stay away from this place!
